WEBVTT

01:10.658 --> 01:12.118
Leave the food and go.

01:25.131 --> 01:28.134
My uncle says I must beg your forgiveness
for deceiving you.

01:28.218 --> 01:29.803
Your uncle?

01:29.886 --> 01:31.262
Prince Baelor.

01:31.346 --> 01:33.014
The heir to the Iron Throne.

01:36.226 --> 01:38.895
-I never meant to lie.
-Yeah, but you did.

01:38.978 --> 01:41.815
About everything, starting with your name.

01:41.898 --> 01:43.650
I've not heard of a Prince Egg.

01:43.733 --> 01:46.111
-Short for Aegon.
-Of course.

01:46.194 --> 01:47.654
After the Conqueror?

01:49.155 --> 01:51.324
How many Aegons have been king?

01:51.407 --> 01:54.202
Four. Four Aegons.

01:58.873 --> 01:59.874
So why'd you do it?

02:01.584 --> 02:02.710
Was it some jape?

02:04.129 --> 02:05.964
Make a fool of the stupid hedge knight?

02:06.756 --> 02:09.550
No. I was supposed to squire for Daeron.

02:09.633 --> 02:11.052
He's my older brother.

02:11.803 --> 02:13.721
He's a shit knight, and a drunk.

02:13.805 --> 02:15.723
And he didn't want to enter the lists.

02:18.768 --> 02:21.437
He only meant for us to hide in that inn
until the tourney was over.

02:21.521 --> 02:24.190
-You shaved your head.
-It was Daeron who shaved it.

02:24.274 --> 02:26.276
Was it Daeron that told me
you were a stable boy?

02:27.610 --> 02:29.070
-I didn't--
-What?

02:30.822 --> 02:32.657
I didn't think I was doing anything wrong.

02:32.740 --> 02:34.450
Of course, you did.

02:35.535 --> 02:36.870
That's why you lied.

02:40.582 --> 02:42.000
Dry your eyes.

02:45.128 --> 02:48.506
I was just so disappointed
when I couldn't go to the tourney--

02:48.590 --> 02:51.551
Oh, we can't have the little prince being
disappointed now, can we?

02:54.637 --> 02:56.556
I just wanted to be
somebody's squire, ser.

02:56.639 --> 02:59.392
You'd have served a donkey,
were it squire-less.

03:01.269 --> 03:02.562
I'm sorry, ser.

03:03.646 --> 03:04.814
Truly am.

03:09.569 --> 03:11.988
It's just a bit of bad luck
we found each other, isn't it?

03:15.200 --> 03:16.868
What will they do with me, Egg?

03:18.703 --> 03:21.623
My uncle wants to see you
after you're done eating.

03:21.706 --> 03:22.832
I'm done now, then.

03:22.916 --> 03:24.959
I've already kicked
one prince in the mouth.

03:25.877 --> 03:27.629
Don't mean to keep another one waiting.

03:59.661 --> 04:00.662
Rise.

04:05.959 --> 04:07.043
Pour Ser Duncan a cup, Aegon.

04:08.962 --> 04:10.338
Try not to spill it on him.

04:13.716 --> 04:15.343
The boy won't spill, Your Grace.

04:17.637 --> 04:18.512
He's a good boy.

04:19.514 --> 04:22.016
Good squire. And he meant no harm.

04:23.309 --> 04:24.811
I know that now.

04:24.894 --> 04:26.938
One need not intend harm to do it.

04:28.481 --> 04:30.108
Aegon should have come to me when he saw

04:30.191 --> 04:31.943
what his brother was doing
to those puppeteers.

04:32.026 --> 04:34.779
-There was no time, Uncle, I--
-Instead, he ran to you, Ser Duncan.

04:34.862 --> 04:36.197
That was no kindness.

04:39.617 --> 04:41.286
I wish Ser Duncan had killed him.

04:42.287 --> 04:43.705
Aerion is your brother.

04:45.414 --> 04:47.333
And the septons say
we must love our brothers.

04:52.797 --> 04:54.215
Aegon, leave us now.

04:55.216 --> 04:56.634
As you will, Your Grace.

05:08.521 --> 05:09.731
How good a knight are you?

05:11.316 --> 05:12.650
How skilled at arms?

05:14.027 --> 05:16.863
Sir Arlan taught me
sword and shield and

05:17.989 --> 05:19.407
how to tilt at rings.

05:26.831 --> 05:29.834
My brother Maekar returned to the castle
a few hours ago.

05:31.461 --> 05:35.840
He found his son Daeron drunk in an inn
a day's ride to the south.

05:38.092 --> 05:40.053
-I know it.
-He told my brother

05:40.136 --> 05:42.638
that a huge robber knight
made off with Aegon.

05:42.722 --> 05:45.266
I fear you have been cast
as this robber knight, ser.

05:45.350 --> 05:46.601
He's lying.

05:46.684 --> 05:49.437
I left that inn four nights past.

05:49.520 --> 05:52.315
Prince Daeron did not pursue
his brother's captor.

05:52.398 --> 05:53.399
Seemingly not.

05:58.446 --> 05:59.614
What of the girl?

05:59.697 --> 06:01.407
By the time Aerion is done
twisting the tale,

06:01.491 --> 06:02.700
it will be high treason.

06:03.368 --> 06:05.745
Treason? By puppetry?

06:05.828 --> 06:07.705
The dragon is the sigil
of the Royal House.

06:07.789 --> 06:08.956
To portray one being slain...

06:09.040 --> 06:10.500
It was surely innocent.

06:10.583 --> 06:13.378
Perhaps, but far from wise,
even in peacetime.

06:13.461 --> 06:16.923
Aerion calls it a veiled attack
on House Targaryen,

06:17.006 --> 06:18.466
an incitement to revolt.

06:18.549 --> 06:20.385
Do you believe that, Your Grace?

06:22.387 --> 06:24.222
One truth is beyond dispute.

06:24.305 --> 06:26.599
You laid hands upon
the Blood of the Dragon.

06:26.682 --> 06:29.310
The girl's finger was snapped in half.

06:29.394 --> 06:32.438
No matter the cause, it is never wise
to strike a king's grandson.

06:32.522 --> 06:33.940
Would you not have done the same?

06:34.023 --> 06:35.650
I might have.

06:35.733 --> 06:38.027
But I'm a prince of the realm,
not a hedge knight.

06:39.570 --> 06:41.280
Don't all knights make the same oath?

06:43.950 --> 06:45.243
To protect the innocent?

06:56.129 --> 06:58.589
Aerion would like your head
for what you did to him.

07:01.300 --> 07:04.512
He will not have it,
but I cannot deny him a trial.

07:05.471 --> 07:08.641
And with Daeron's accusation
that you kidnaped Egg,

07:08.724 --> 07:10.893
the court is unlikely
to rule in your favor.

07:10.977 --> 07:12.478
And when I'm found guilty?

07:12.562 --> 07:14.397
The last time a man
struck the royal blood,

07:14.480 --> 07:16.816
it was decreed he should lose
the offending hand.

07:17.900 --> 07:19.694
And you kicked him, too, did you not?

07:21.487 --> 07:22.530
I did.

07:25.158 --> 07:26.409
You have another choice.

07:27.326 --> 07:29.787
Whether it is a better one
or a worse, I cannot say.

07:29.871 --> 07:33.416
And so, I ask you again,
Ser Duncan the Tall,

07:34.250 --> 07:37.253
how good a knight are you, truly?

08:07.158 --> 08:08.826
Trial by combat.

08:11.454 --> 08:12.622
That is my right.

08:17.877 --> 08:19.170
I refuse.

08:20.796 --> 08:23.007
You cannot refuse.

08:23.090 --> 08:26.010
Any knight accused of a crime
has the right to demand as such.

08:26.844 --> 08:28.638
Unless you withdraw your claim?

08:34.101 --> 08:35.436
A trial of seven.

08:40.232 --> 08:42.025
That is my right, I do believe.

08:42.109 --> 08:43.528
What the fuck is a trial of seven?

08:49.492 --> 08:51.327
It is another form of trial by combat.

08:52.954 --> 08:55.998
Ancient. Seldom invoked.

08:56.082 --> 08:59.377
It came across the Narrow Sea
with the Andals and their seven gods.

09:00.378 --> 09:03.256
Well, if it was the Andals...

09:04.340 --> 09:06.425
I'm sorry, Your Grace.

09:06.968 --> 09:09.345
The old man was never much for praying.

09:09.428 --> 09:12.640
What is a trial of seven?

09:13.724 --> 09:16.060
The Andals believed
that if seven champions fought,

09:16.143 --> 09:18.771
the gods, being thus honored,
would be more like to intervene

09:20.022 --> 09:21.607
and see the guilty party punished.

09:26.487 --> 09:30.533
Are you cowering behind some
6,000-year-old Andal foolery

09:30.616 --> 09:34.161
because you're afraid to face
this hedge knight alone?

09:34.245 --> 09:35.746
-No.
-Then why?

09:36.789 --> 09:38.791
Why not slay the rogue yourself?

09:42.003 --> 09:43.545
Daeron has been wronged as well.

09:43.629 --> 09:47.383
Ser Duncan must pay
for each one of his crimes against us.

09:47.466 --> 09:51.095
Or would we leave a matter
of Targaryen honor in doubt?

09:51.178 --> 09:53.097
Do not speak to me of honor, boy.

09:53.180 --> 09:55.099
This is fucking nonsense.

09:55.182 --> 09:56.350
Is it?

09:58.019 --> 09:59.353
No.

10:06.569 --> 10:09.989
Aerion is within his rights.
We have no choice.

10:11.198 --> 10:13.784
A trial of seven must be held at dawn.

10:13.868 --> 10:16.954
What does that mean?
That I must fight seven men?

10:17.038 --> 10:18.581
Do not play the fool.

10:18.664 --> 10:20.499
It must be seven against seven.

10:21.125 --> 10:23.669
You must find six other knights
to fight beside you.

10:23.753 --> 10:25.212
But I have no one else.

10:25.296 --> 10:28.549
If a cause is just,
good men will fight for it.

10:29.675 --> 10:31.927
If not, it will be because you are guilty.

10:43.522 --> 10:44.899
Come here.

10:54.408 --> 10:55.701
Idiot!

11:00.206 --> 11:01.749
Can I go now?

11:07.797 --> 11:10.341
Seek your champions, Ser Duncan.

11:42.123 --> 11:43.082
Oh, lads.

11:45.793 --> 11:47.169
I've mucked it up this time.

11:48.129 --> 11:51.006
-I think I'm gonna die tomorrow.
-Dunk!

11:51.716 --> 11:54.343
Is that you? You're alive.

12:00.599 --> 12:02.393
Raymun, thank you for watching my--

12:02.476 --> 12:03.811
Are you hungry?

12:04.937 --> 12:06.605
-No, not really.
-Come on.

12:08.441 --> 12:11.026
-Whoa!
-Were you talking to your horses?

12:11.110 --> 12:13.738
-Yeah.
-That's fucking mad.

12:15.906 --> 12:16.991
Trial of seven.

12:17.074 --> 12:21.036
Duncan, that means battleaxes,
morningstars, and lances of war.

12:21.120 --> 12:23.122
-I know what it means.
-I apologize.

12:23.205 --> 12:25.291
Seems cousin here has milk in his veins.

12:25.374 --> 12:28.127
-Oh, fuck off, I just meant--
-This is knightly combat, Raymun.

12:28.210 --> 12:30.629
As you are no knight,
your skin is not at risk.

12:34.508 --> 12:36.552
I saw what Aerion did to those puppeteers.

12:37.636 --> 12:39.597
All knights vow to protect the innocent.

12:40.014 --> 12:41.307
Even hedge knights, I assume.

12:44.310 --> 12:45.603
I'm for you.

12:49.273 --> 12:50.900
Thank you, ser.

12:54.111 --> 12:57.364
-Perhaps you shouldn't.
-It pains me to admit it,

12:57.448 --> 12:58.866
but Steffon's a fine sword.

12:58.949 --> 13:01.243
-Why would that pain you?
-I don't doubt that.

13:01.952 --> 13:04.455
But the Dragon House will not look kindly
on those who oppose them.

13:04.538 --> 13:05.873
Dragon House?

13:07.166 --> 13:08.751
Where are their dragons, Ser Duncan?

13:10.461 --> 13:12.004
Us Fossoways, we were here

13:12.087 --> 13:14.548
long before these others
come to our shores.

13:14.632 --> 13:16.842
And I'll warrant we'll be here
long after they are gone.

13:18.552 --> 13:21.639
-Who else fights with us?
-I know no one else.

13:22.973 --> 13:26.060
I'm sure we can find five more good men
who wish singers to make them immortal.

13:27.436 --> 13:31.232
I do not know why tragedy
so oft follows after honorable men.

13:32.233 --> 13:34.443
But when I find myself
without the answers,

13:34.527 --> 13:36.987
the answer is always "more glory."

13:38.906 --> 13:40.866
Lucky for you, I have some friends.

13:40.950 --> 13:42.910
Ser Lyonel, Lord Lannister, Ser Otho.

13:42.993 --> 13:45.037
They won't be happy at being woken.

13:45.120 --> 13:46.705
Then they'll fight like pestered badgers.

13:48.374 --> 13:50.751
You shan't die under my watch, ser.

13:51.585 --> 13:52.670
I promise you that.

14:16.235 --> 14:20.364
Raymun, do you think your cousin
can bring the men he speaks of?

14:21.323 --> 14:22.741
I don't know.

14:25.703 --> 14:26.996
You may be wise to run.

14:27.746 --> 14:29.331
Won't they kill me if I run?

14:29.415 --> 14:30.958
Won't they kill you anyway?

14:35.295 --> 14:37.548
Maybe the gods figure
this is what I deserve.

14:38.549 --> 14:40.259
For doing what you were supposed to do?

14:43.429 --> 14:44.972
For not knowing my place.

14:48.058 --> 14:50.269
-Ser.
-Egg!

14:51.854 --> 14:52.855
What are you doing?

14:53.939 --> 14:56.609
I'm your squire, ser.
You'll need someone to arm you.

14:58.319 --> 15:00.321
Does your father know
you've left the castle?

15:00.404 --> 15:01.864
I hope not.

15:04.783 --> 15:07.912
I don't think I could bear
another foot whipping tonight.

15:10.873 --> 15:13.334
-You!
-No! No, Duncan, no!

15:13.417 --> 15:15.419
Stop! Please!

15:15.502 --> 15:16.837
Are you mad coming here?

15:16.921 --> 15:19.089
I should drive this through your neck.

15:19.173 --> 15:20.716
I'd sooner you pour me a cup of wine.

15:20.799 --> 15:23.427
Fuck your wine. You lied about me.

15:24.178 --> 15:26.263
Well, I had to say something
when my father

15:26.347 --> 15:28.724
demanded to know where Egg had gotten to.

15:29.725 --> 15:31.393
Please, don't hurt him.

15:34.772 --> 15:36.523
He can't kill me twice.

15:38.108 --> 15:40.069
My father's going to join
the seven accusers, ser.

15:40.152 --> 15:43.197
Yeah, of course he will.
He must redeem his sons' honor.

15:43.280 --> 15:45.115
Not that I ever asked
to have my honor redeemed.

15:45.824 --> 15:48.118
Whoever has it can keep it,
so far as I'm concerned.

15:48.202 --> 15:50.537
I begged him not to, ser. I begged him.

15:51.664 --> 15:54.291
For what it's worth,
you have little to fear from me,

15:54.375 --> 15:56.502
and I'll do my best to look
gallant in the first charge.

15:56.585 --> 16:00.381
But after that, perhaps
you could strike me a nice blow

16:00.464 --> 16:02.466
to the side of the helm.

16:02.549 --> 16:04.218
Make it ring. Not too loud.

16:04.301 --> 16:06.762
Is that all you came here to say?

16:10.307 --> 16:12.559
My father has commanded
the Kingsguard to fight as well.

16:16.146 --> 16:17.439
Only the three that are here.

16:17.523 --> 16:18.941
Who do you have, ser?

16:20.484 --> 16:21.902
Raymun's cousin.

16:27.992 --> 16:30.786
I can bring people, ser. Knights. I can.

16:31.912 --> 16:33.580
I'll be fighting against your family.

16:33.664 --> 16:36.250
My father will be well guarded,
and you won't kill Daeron.

16:36.333 --> 16:38.293
He told you he'd fall down.

16:42.047 --> 16:43.424
And Aerion.

16:44.800 --> 16:45.968
You'd see him dead?

16:46.969 --> 16:48.554
When I was little,

16:48.637 --> 16:51.265
Aerion used to come
into my bed chamber at night,

16:51.348 --> 16:53.392
put his knife in between my legs.

16:53.475 --> 16:55.519
He had too many brothers, he'd say.

16:55.602 --> 16:58.522
Maybe one night, he'd make me his sister.
Then he could marry me.

17:02.985 --> 17:04.277
Sorry, that was...

17:04.361 --> 17:05.946
Egg has the truth of it.

17:06.030 --> 17:07.739
Aerion can be quite the monster.

17:07.823 --> 17:09.949
And he threw my cat in the well, too.

17:10.034 --> 17:12.619
-He says he didn't, but he did.
-Alright.

17:14.662 --> 17:16.957
He thinks he's a dragon in human form.

17:17.041 --> 17:18.624
That's why he was so wroth
at the puppet show.

17:18.709 --> 17:20.669
A pity he wasn't born a Fossoway.

17:20.753 --> 17:23.046
Then he'd think himself an apple
and we'd all be a deal safer.

17:25.882 --> 17:26.925
I must steal back to the castle.

17:28.093 --> 17:29.303
Ser Duncan?

17:30.304 --> 17:31.388
Private word?

17:50.407 --> 17:51.617
I dreamed of you.

17:53.118 --> 17:54.620
You said that.

17:56.205 --> 17:58.415
-At the inn.
-Did I?

18:00.334 --> 18:03.045
Well, my dreams
are not like yours.

18:04.254 --> 18:05.631
Mine come true.

18:07.132 --> 18:09.843
An impressive talent
for an unimpressive man.

18:09.927 --> 18:11.637
Another one of life's little ironies.

18:14.056 --> 18:15.641
But I have seen you, ser.

18:16.934 --> 18:18.102
And a fire.

18:19.561 --> 18:20.813
And a dead dragon.

18:23.273 --> 18:28.195
A great beast with wings so large
they could cover this meadow.

18:29.404 --> 18:31.448
It had fallen on top of you.

18:31.532 --> 18:34.660
But you were alive,
and the dragon was dead.

18:37.996 --> 18:39.248
Did I kill it?

18:41.959 --> 18:43.877
That I could not say.

18:45.879 --> 18:47.673
We were dragon masters once.

18:49.258 --> 18:51.802
Hard to believe.

18:51.885 --> 18:53.846
Now, they're all gone, but we remain.

18:57.474 --> 18:58.934
I don't care to die today.

19:01.728 --> 19:03.355
I don't care to die either.

19:07.651 --> 19:10.195
It may be that I've killed you
with my lie.

19:10.279 --> 19:12.406
And if so, I'm sorry.

19:13.949 --> 19:16.618
I'm doomed to some kind of hell, I know.

19:18.954 --> 19:20.247
Likely one without wine.

19:34.970 --> 19:36.763
You are no knight.

19:47.649 --> 19:49.276
You are Florian the Fool.

20:13.550 --> 20:14.801
Ser Duncan.

20:15.636 --> 20:19.056
If you are come for your shield,
she left it with me.

20:36.949 --> 20:38.700
Where did she go?

20:40.577 --> 20:41.703
They make for Dorne.

20:42.871 --> 20:44.498
Well gone is well forgot.

20:45.624 --> 20:46.667
Good.

21:05.394 --> 21:06.895
Your rim was old.

21:08.063 --> 21:11.400
Cheap steel. Brittle and rusted.

21:11.483 --> 21:13.026
I've made you a new one.

21:13.610 --> 21:14.778
It's twice as thick.

21:14.861 --> 21:16.530
I've put some straps on the back.

21:18.323 --> 21:22.119
It will be heavier now, but stronger too.

21:26.415 --> 21:27.916
The girl did the paint.

21:30.919 --> 21:32.587
The star is fallen.

21:32.671 --> 21:35.966
And the sunset heralds night.

21:37.718 --> 21:40.137
The shield is all painted up
like death.

21:43.307 --> 21:44.933
The elm's alive, man.

21:46.184 --> 21:48.312
See how green the leaves are?

21:48.395 --> 21:49.938
That's summer leaves, for certain.

21:52.024 --> 21:53.734
You remember the old shield rhyme?

21:57.321 --> 21:59.406
Oak and iron, guard me well.

22:01.158 --> 22:03.035
Or else I'm dead and doomed to hell.

22:05.746 --> 22:06.997
Mm.

22:16.423 --> 22:20.302
How much do you want
for the new rim and all?

22:21.970 --> 22:23.221
From you...

22:25.891 --> 22:26.975
a copper.

23:04.429 --> 23:05.430
Sers...

23:07.224 --> 23:08.433
I am in your debt.

23:08.517 --> 23:10.769
The debt is Aerion's.

23:11.770 --> 23:13.146
And we mean to collect it.

23:14.356 --> 23:16.858
-I had heard your leg was broken.
-You heard true.

23:16.942 --> 23:18.860
My leg is broken, I cannot walk.

23:19.820 --> 23:23.156
But so long as I can sit
on a horse, I can fight.

23:23.573 --> 23:25.992
Ser Robyn would die
the king's faithful servant.

23:26.660 --> 23:30.539
But when the crown goes against the gods,
Ser Robyn goes against the crown.

23:32.082 --> 23:33.750
I always knew you meant trouble.

23:35.836 --> 23:38.004
-I cannot thank you enough.
-Ah.

23:38.088 --> 23:40.132
Nor Ser Steffon for bringing you.

23:40.215 --> 23:42.884
Who the fuck is Ser Stevron? Your...

23:42.968 --> 23:44.803
...boy found me.

23:44.886 --> 23:47.013
Hasn't been a trial of seven
for a hundred years.

23:47.097 --> 23:49.558
I wasn't about to miss a chance
to bloody up the Kingsguard

23:49.641 --> 23:51.435
in their pretty white gowns.

24:46.990 --> 24:49.826
Six. There are only six.

24:49.910 --> 24:51.786
Is it possible Aerion
has not found a seventh

24:51.870 --> 24:53.163
to take up his claim?

24:53.246 --> 24:55.165
Raymun!

24:55.248 --> 24:56.541
My helm, if you please.

24:58.376 --> 25:00.504
Ser Steffon, what of your friends?

25:01.505 --> 25:03.131
We only need one more to make our seven.

25:03.215 --> 25:04.925
I'm afraid you'll need two more.

25:09.137 --> 25:11.431
I fight with Prince Aerion
and the accusers.

25:17.562 --> 25:18.730
No, you...

25:19.856 --> 25:21.274
you told Ser Duncan to rely on you.

25:21.358 --> 25:24.152
Well, our prince would not have
made me a lord elsewise,

25:24.236 --> 25:25.820
but for it thwarted Ser Duncan.

25:29.074 --> 25:31.117
You traded your honor for a lordship?

25:31.952 --> 25:33.495
Cousin.

25:33.578 --> 25:36.289
I know great men who have traded
their honor for far less.

25:36.373 --> 25:38.458
It was a bargain well struck.

25:40.502 --> 25:41.920
Fetch me my horse.

25:45.423 --> 25:46.883
Get him yourself.

26:08.113 --> 26:09.739
We are lost.

26:15.370 --> 26:18.206
Knight me. I will take my cousin's place.

26:23.211 --> 26:24.671
Ser Duncan, knight me.

26:25.672 --> 26:27.549
Raymun, I shouldn't.

26:27.632 --> 26:28.883
Without me, you're only five.

26:29.926 --> 26:31.803
You cannot win with five.

26:33.972 --> 26:36.433
The lad has the truth of it, I'm afraid.

26:38.059 --> 26:39.936
Go on, Ser Duncan.

26:40.020 --> 26:41.521
Any knight can make a knight.

26:56.411 --> 26:57.912
Go.

26:57.996 --> 26:59.831
I shall give Squire Raymun his knighthood.

27:11.092 --> 27:14.888
In the name of the Warrior,
I charge you to be brave.

27:22.270 --> 27:26.024
In the name of the Father,
I charge you to be just.

27:32.072 --> 27:34.032
In the name of the Mother...

27:35.033 --> 27:37.702
I charge you to protect
the young and innocent.

27:50.632 --> 27:51.716
Ser Duncan.

27:53.051 --> 27:54.386
We cannot delay any further.

27:55.053 --> 27:57.681
-Seems you only have five champions.
-Six.

27:57.764 --> 28:00.016
Ser Lyonel is knighting Raymun Fossoway.

28:00.100 --> 28:01.643
We will fight you six against seven.

28:01.726 --> 28:03.520
I'm afraid it is not permitted.

28:03.603 --> 28:05.814
If you cannot find another
knight to join you, ser,

28:05.897 --> 28:08.024
then you must be declared
guilty of your crimes.

28:11.903 --> 28:13.780
M'lord, I beg a moment, please.

28:15.198 --> 28:16.616
You have it.

28:47.522 --> 28:48.732
M'lords!

28:50.775 --> 28:54.028
I know none of you remember
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

28:56.531 --> 28:57.991
But I was his squire.

29:00.326 --> 29:01.828
We served many of you.

29:04.664 --> 29:06.124
Ate at your tables.

29:07.250 --> 29:08.543
Slept in your halls.

29:14.549 --> 29:15.925
He was a good man.

29:18.803 --> 29:20.597
And he taught me how to be a knight.

29:24.434 --> 29:27.020
Not just sword and lance, but honor.

29:31.149 --> 29:33.151
A knight defends the innocent.

29:34.527 --> 29:36.988
That's-- that's all I did.

29:41.618 --> 29:46.039
I was not Ser Arlan's blood,
but I have followed his example.

29:47.582 --> 29:50.043
As your sons will follow yours.

30:02.263 --> 30:04.516
Who will stand and fight with me?

30:21.449 --> 30:22.784
The Brute of Bracken!

30:53.731 --> 30:58.403
Has courage deserted
the noble houses of Westeros?

30:59.362 --> 31:01.406
I will not believe it is so!

31:06.703 --> 31:09.247
Are there no true knights among you?!

31:33.479 --> 31:35.523
I will take Ser Duncan's side.

31:49.120 --> 31:50.955
Have you taken leave of your senses?

31:52.123 --> 31:53.458
This man attacked my son.

31:53.541 --> 31:55.376
This man protected the innocent.

31:56.878 --> 31:58.338
As every true knight must.

31:59.255 --> 32:01.799
Let the gods decide
if he was right or wrong.

32:01.883 --> 32:02.884
Hyah!
